OL,3,C'Patients are dying in corridors': NHS
OL,4,Cworker reveals hospital chaos
OL,6,FIncreasingly, hospital patients are
OL,7,Fbeing treated in non-clinical areas,
OL,8,Fsuch as corridors, cupboards or
OL,9,Foffices, while they wait for a bed on
OL,10,Fa ward to become available.
OL,12,F"I feel ashamed that I'm allowing
OL,13,Fpatients to be treated in this way,"
OL,14,Fthe NHS staff member told ITV News.
OL,16,F"It's like it's normal - and it's not
OL,17,Fnormal. Patients are dying in
OL,18,Fcorridors, and we're just watching
OL,19,Fpeople die, and there's nothing we can
OL,20,Fdo about it."
