OL,3,C'Patients are dying in corridors': NHS
OL,4,Cworker reveals hospital chaos
OL,6,FElsewhere, Bernard Parkinson, 75, from
OL,7,FChorley in Lancashire, spent three
OL,8,Fdays on a hospital corridor while he
OL,9,Fwas being treated for sepsis.
OL,11,FIt happened last August - not during
OL,12,Fthe usually pressured winter period.
OL,14,FBernard's daughter, Sharron Smith,
OL,15,Fdescribed their experience at Royal
OL,16,FPreston Hospital as "carnage".
OL,18,F"There were people everywhere. The
OL,19,Fstaff were running up and down. There
OL,20,Fwas no privacy at all," Sharron told
OL,21,FITV News.
