OL,3,C'Patients are dying in corridors': NHS
OL,4,Cworker reveals hospital chaos
OL,6,F"As a system, we work together to
OL,7,Fmanage risks to patients, which means
OL,8,Fprioritising the release of ambulances
OL,9,Fback onto the road to react to 999
OL,10,Fcalls. This, alongside a high volume
OL,11,Fof critically ill patients and limited
OL,12,Fbed capacity within our own and
OL,13,Fsurrounding hospitals and within the
OL,14,Fcommunity, can lead to corridor care,
OL,15,Fwhich is something none of us want for
OL,16,Four patients.
